 <body>
  <blockquote>
   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    <span style="font-weight: 400">
     <font face="Arial">
      FOOL
     </font>
    </span>
   </p>
   <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    <span style="background-color: #FFFF00">
     Note: there is a difference between 
	the signs "to fool" and "a fool."
    </span>
   </p>
   <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    <span style="font-weight: 400">
     <br/>
     "To fool someone."
    </span>
   </p>
   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    <span style="font-weight: 400">
     <img border="0" height="229" src="/images/foolsomeone1.jpg" width="199"/>
     <img border="0" height="229" src="/images/foolsomeone2.jpg" width="199"/>
     <img border="0" height="229" src="/images/foolsomeone3.jpg" width="199"/>
    </span>
   </p>
   <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    <span style="font-weight: 400">
     <br/>
     "Do you like to fool people?"
     <br/>
    </span>
   </p>
   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    <br/>
   </p>
   <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    <span style="font-weight: 400">
     Discussion:  If you wanted to say that someone is "a fool" you would sign, "HE SILLY," "HE DUMB," or "HE STUPID" depending on your
  meaning.
    </span>
   </p>
   <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
